Rainstorm and moderate gusty winds last 48 hours.

Sunny- calm- air temp = 75 F. Green algae bloom uniform- poor water clarity.  State Park and Campground- homes along shore.  pH = 9.30; surface temp = 76.4 F; btm temp at 12' = 64.6 F. Surface D.O = 12.5. { PO4 = 0.1; NO3 = 0.1; NH3 = 0.1; Alk = 180; Chloride = 40;  TDS = 140 (ea in mg/L)}; Cond. = 0.21 m/S
Called and had aerators turned on for Mirror Lake- due to the low oxygen readings.

Sunny- calm- 70F. Sampling point at bluff along narrows- bottom depth = 10 ft.pH= 8.00; conductivity=0.23 uS/cm; TDS= 150 mg/L; PO4 (Chemet) less than 0.1 mg/L; alkalinity= 100 mg/L. Dense floating mats of algae common.  Species present: Spirogyra and oscillatoria.
Collected water sample to send to UWSP.
